The joint density cannot be factorized as 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{X,Y}(x,y)=g(x)g(y)$
\end_inset

 so 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 are not independent.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Compute the marginal density of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

.
 Does it belong to any of the known distributions?
\begin_inset space \hspace{}
\length 1cm
\end_inset

1p.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

[
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Solution
\series default
:
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

]
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
f_{X}(x) & =\int_{0}^{1}(1+x)y^{x}\exp(-x)dy=(1+x)\exp(-x)\int_{0}^{1}y^{x}dy\\
 & =(1+x)\exp(-x)\left[\frac{1}{1+x}y^{x+1}\right]_{0}^{1}=(1+x)\exp(-x)\frac{1}{1+x}=\exp(-x)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

so 
\begin_inset Formula $X\sim Exp(1)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Compute the conditional density of 
\begin_inset Formula $Y|X=x$
\end_inset

.
 Does it belong to any of the known distributions?
\begin_inset space \hspace{}
\length 1cm
\end_inset

1.5p.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

[
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Solution
\series default
:
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

]
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{Y|X=x}(y)=\frac{f_{X,Y}(x,y)}{f_{X}(x)}=\frac{(1+x)y^{x}\exp(-x)}{\exp(-x)}=(1+x)y^{x}=(1+x)y^{x+1-1}(1-y)^{b-1}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $b=1$
\end_inset

.
 Note that this looks like a 
\begin_inset Formula $Beta(x+1,1)$
\end_inset

 density, if we can show that the normalizing constant of this density is
 
\begin_inset Formula $(1+x)$
\end_inset

.
 The normalizing constant of the 
\begin_inset Formula $Beta(x+1,1)$
\end_inset

 density is
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\Gamma(x+1+1)}{\Gamma(x+1)\Gamma(1)}=\frac{\Gamma(x+2)}{\Gamma(x+1)}=\frac{(x+1)\Gamma(x+1)}{\Gamma(x+1)}=1+x
\]

\end_inset

since 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma(a+1)=a\Gamma(a)$
\end_inset

 for any 
\begin_inset Formula $a>0$
\end_inset

.
 Thus, 
\begin_inset Formula $Y|X=x\sim Beta(x+1,1)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Compute 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left[(X+2)Y\right]$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset space \hspace{}
\length 1cm
\end_inset

1.5p.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

[
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series bold
Solution
\series default
:
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

]
\end_layout

\end_inset

By the law of iterated expectation
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
E\left[(X+2)Y\right] & =EE\left[(X+2)Y|X\right]=E\left((X+2)E\left[Y|X\right]\right)\\
 & =E\left((X+2)\frac{X+1}{X+2}\right)=E\left(X+1\right)=1+1=2
\end{align*}

\end_inset

since 
\begin_inset Formula $Y|X=x\sim Beta(x+1,1)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $X\sim Exp(1)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
