\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
From 4a) we know that the joint density is
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{U,V}(u,v)=\frac{1}{\Gamma(\alpha)\Gamma(\beta)}u^{\alpha+\beta-1}e^{-u}v{}^{\alpha-1}(1-v){}^{\beta-1}
\]

\end_inset

which directly shows (because of the independence) that the marginal density
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 is proportional to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v{}^{\alpha-1}(1-v){}^{\beta-1}
\]

\end_inset

which implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $V=X/(X+Y)\sim Beta(\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

.
