\begin_layout Enumerate
What is the moment generating function of 
\begin_inset Formula $Z=\frac{c\cdot(X+Y)^{2}+d\cdot X}{X+Y}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 are positive constants?
\begin_inset space \hspace{}
\length 1cm
\end_inset

2p.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Note that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z=c\cdot(X+Y)+d\frac{X}{X+Y}=cU+dV
\]

\end_inset

and the we know from 4a that 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 are independent.
 The moment generating function of 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 is
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
E(e^{tZ})=E\left[e^{t\left(c\cdot U+dV\right)}\right]=E\left[e^{tcU}\right]E\left[e^{tdV}\right]=\varphi_{U}(tc)\cdot\varphi_{V}(td)
\]

\end_inset

We know that 
\begin_inset Formula $V\sim Beta(\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

 so 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{V}(\cdot)$
\end_inset

 is the moment generating function of the 
\begin_inset Formula $Beta(\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

.
 We can compute 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{U}(tc)$
\end_inset

 directly from its definition, but we rather try to find the distribution
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 and then read off the moment generating function from the Tables.
 From above, the marginal density of 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 is proportional to 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u^{\alpha+\beta-1}e^{-u}
\]

\end_inset

which means that 
\begin_inset Formula $U\sim\Gamma(\alpha+\beta,1)$
\end_inset

 and so
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\varphi_{U}(t)=\frac{1}{(1-t)^{\alpha+\beta}}
\]

\end_inset

for 
\begin_inset Formula $t<1$
\end_inset

.
 Thus
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
E(e^{tZ})=\frac{1}{(1-tc)^{\alpha+\beta}}\cdot\varphi_{V}(td),
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi_{V}(t)$
\end_inset

 is the moment generating function of the 
\begin_inset Formula $Beta(\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

